ForgeRL - Third-Party Notices
=============================

This project incorporates or depends on the following third-party
software and data, each with their own licensing terms.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
Forge - MTG Rules Engine
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Source: https://github.com/Card-Forge/forge
Fork:   https://github.com/RexGoliath1/forge.git (branch: feature/rl-daemon-mode)
License: GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPL-3.0)

Forge is an unofficial rules engine for Magic: The Gathering, developed
by the Forge community. Our fork contains modifications for daemon mode
operation. Forge source code is available at the URLs above.

ForgeRL communicates with Forge as a separate process via TCP sockets.
The ForgeRL Python codebase is an independent work and is not a
derivative of Forge.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scryfall
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Source: https://scryfall.com
API Docs: https://scryfall.com/docs/api
License: Scryfall data used under Wizards of the Coast Fan Content Policy

Card data and images are provided by Scryfall. Card images are
copyright Wizards of the Coast. Scryfall is not affiliated with this
project.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
17lands
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Source: https://www.17lands.com
Datasets: https://www.17lands.com/public_datasets
License: CC BY 4.0

Public game replay data from 17lands is used for behavioral cloning
training. Attribution: 17lands.com

